Ingredients.1: 3 pounds skinless, boneless chicken breast meat

Ingredients.2: 1 (10.5 ounce) can condensed cream of chicken soup

Ingredients.3: 1 (10.5 ounce) can condensed cream of celery soup

Ingredients.5: 1 (6 ounce) package seasoned cornbread stuffing mix

Directions.1: Place chicken in a large saucepan full of lightly salted water. Bring to a boil. Boil until chicken is cooked through (juices run clear), about 30 minutes. Remove chicken from pan, reserving broth.

Directions.2: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and place in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.

Directions.3: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).

Directions.4: Mix together condensed soups in a medium bowl. Fill one empty soup can with milk and mix milk with soups. Pour mixture over chicken.

Directions.5: Combine stuffing and broth in a small bowl; mix together and spoon the mixture over the casserole.

Directions.6: Bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes.
